Bootstrap

11/11/2020

Bootstrap

Bootstrap for median

n = 1000
X = rnorm(n) 
X_med = median(X)

B = 10000
X_med_BT = rep(NA, B) 

for(i_BT in 1:B){
  w = sample(n,n,replace=T) 
  X_BT = X[w]
  X_med_BT[i_BT] = median(X_BT)
}

Confidence interval using normal approximation:

X_med_BT_mean = mean(X_med_BT)

X_med_BT_VAR = var(X_med_BT)

X_med_BT_mean - 1.96 * sqrt(X_med_BT_VAR)
## [1] -0.07377954
X_med_BT_mean + 1.96 * sqrt(X_med_BT_VAR)
## [1] 0.09879919

Confidence interval based on quantiles of bootstrap:

quantile(X_med_BT,c(0.025,0.975))
##        2.5%       97.5% 
## -0.07814580  0.08763178

Bootstrap in Regression

Empirical bootstrap

n = nrow(mtcars) 
B = 1000
coeff_BT = matrix(NA, nrow=B, ncol=3) 
for(i_BT in 1:B){
  w = sample(n,n,replace=T)
  data_BT = mtcars[w,]
  fit_BT = lm(mpg~wt+disp, data=data_BT) 
  coeff_BT[i_BT,] = coef(fit_BT)
}

quantile(coeff_BT[,1],c(0.025,0.975))
##     2.5%    97.5% 
## 30.41302 40.07984
quantile(coeff_BT[,2],c(0.025,0.975))
##      2.5%     97.5% 
## -5.798529 -1.231509
quantile(coeff_BT[,3],c(0.025,0.975))
##        2.5%       97.5% 
## -0.03476841 -0.00165709

Use boot package

library(boot)
# function to obtain regression weights
bs <- function(formula, data, indices) {
  d <- data[indices,] # allows boot to select sample
  fit <- lm(formula, data=d)
  return(coef(fit))
}
# bootstrapping with 1000 replications
results <- boot(data=mtcars, statistic = bs,
   R=1000, formula=mpg~wt+disp)

# view results
results
## 
## ORDINARY NONPARAMETRIC BOOTSTRAP
## 
## 
## Call:
## boot(data = mtcars, statistic = bs, R = 1000, formula = mpg ~ 
##     wt + disp)
## 
## 
## Bootstrap Statistics :
##        original        bias    std. error
## t1* 34.96055404  2.786945e-01 2.561622181
## t2* -3.35082533 -1.074968e-01 1.170126747
## t3* -0.01772474  5.312197e-07 0.008477937
plot(results, index=1) # intercept

plot(results, index=2) # wt

plot(results, index=3) # disp

# get 95% confidence intervals
boot.ci(results, type="bca", index=1) # intercept

Residual bootstrap

#fit model using the original data
fit = lm(mpg~wt+disp, data=mtcars) 
y_predict = predict(fit)

coeff_BT_res = matrix(NA, nrow=B, ncol=3) 
for(i_BT in 1:B){
  w = sample(n,n,replace=T)
  y_bt = y_predict+fit$residuals[w]
  data_BT = data.frame(y_bt, wt=mtcars$wt, disp=mtcars$disp)
  fit_BT = lm(y_bt~wt+disp, data=data_BT)
  coeff_BT_res[i_BT,] = coef(fit_BT)
  }

quantile(coeff_BT_res[,1],c(0.025,0.975))
##     2.5%    97.5% 
## 31.12300 38.97416
quantile(coeff_BT_res[,2],c(0.025,0.975))
##      2.5%     97.5% 
## -5.361982 -1.254013
quantile(coeff_BT_res[,3],c(0.025,0.975)) 
##         2.5%        97.5% 
## -0.034968043 -0.001805877
